==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''scortat-'', from [[scortari]] ‘associate with prostitutes’, from [[scortum]] ‘prostitute’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /skɔ:'teɪtəri/

===Adjective===
'''scortatory'''
# pertaining to [[scortation]]; [[lewd]], [[fornicatory]]
#:*'''1922''': Twenty years he dallied there between conjugal love and its chaste delights and '''scortatory''' love and its foul pleasures. — James Joyce, ''Ulysses''